The paper discusses a semantic criterion for strong normalization of theories expressed in minimal deduction modulo, which is a topic related to logic and type theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The use of Curry-style proof-terms and pre-Heyting algebras also suggests that cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LF (Logic in Computer Science) are relevant sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the completeness of the criterion, which is a topic related to formal verification and theorem proving, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the simplicity of the criterion and its proof, which could be relevant to software engineering, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category as well.
